SERVICE AGREEMENT
FOR
FIRM POINT-TO-POINT TRANSMISSION SERVICE
BETWEEN
WILDERNESS LINE HOLDINGS, LLC AND
WINDSTAR ENERGY, LLC Specifications For Long-Term Firm Point-To-Point Transmission Service
1.0 Term of Transaction:
Start Date: June 30, 2020
Termination Date: December 16, 2031
2.0 Description of capacity and energy to be transmitted by Tie Line Owner including the electric Control Area in which the transaction originates.
60 MW of the output of Transmission Customer's interconnecting wind energy facility located in the CAISO balancing area shall be delivered pursuant to the terms of this service agreement.
3.0 Point(s) of Receipt: Wilderness 220 KV Line between poles OC28 and OC30_
Delivering Party: Windstar LLC, Windstar 2 Substation __________________________________
4.0 Point(s) of Delivery: Sagebrush Line at Wilderness Switching Station ______
Receiving Party: Sagebrush____________________________________
5.0 Maximum amount of capacity and energy to be transmitted (Reserved Capacity): ___60 MW________________________________
6.0 Designation of party(ies) subject to reciprocal service obligation:______N/A_______________________________________________ __________________________________________________________________ __________________________________________________________________
7.0 Name(s) of any Intervening Systems providing transmission service:______N/A__________________________________________________ __________________________________________________________________
8.0 Service under this Agreement may be subject to some combination of the charges detailed below. (The appropriate charges for individual transactions will be determined in accordance with the terms and conditions of the Tariff.)
8.1 Transmission Charge: Rate set forth in Schedule 7 of the Tariff, per agreement by Transmission Customer and Tie Line Owners predecessor in interest, Sky River LLC, to be paid in two installments based on the net present value of the rate when paid. Transmission Customer made an initial payment of $2 million for an initial term of ten (10) years of service through December 16, 2021. Per agreement by the parties, Transmission Customer shall make a second payment of $2.46 million (subject to adjustment to reflect the net present value of the rate set forth in Schedule 7 of the Tariff when paid) to Tie Line Owner no later than April 30, 2022, for the remainder of the term of service under this Agreement.
8.2 System Impact and/or Facilities Study Charge(s): ___N/A___________________________________________ __________________________________________________
8.3 Direct Assignment Facilities Charge: ____N/A_____________ __________________________________________________
8.4 Ancillary Services Charges: ___N/A____________________ __________________________________________________ __________________________________________________ __________________________________________________ __________________________________________________ __________________________________________________ __________________________________________________
Note: deposit requirement was waived due to circumstances of transmission service request, including adoption of OATT following FERC order. ATTACHMENT A Form Of Service Agreement For Firm Point-To-Point Transmission Service
1.0 This Service Agreement, dated as of June 30, 2020, is entered into, by and between Wilderness Line Holdings, LLC (Wilderness Holdings or the Tie Line Owner), and Windstar Energy, LLC (Windstar Energy or the Transmission Customer).
2.0 The Transmission Customer has been determined by the Tie Line Owner to have a Completed Application for Firm Point-To-Point Transmission Service under the Tariff.
3.0 The Transmission Customer has provided to the Tie Line Owner an Application deposit in accordance with the provisions of Section 17.3 of the Tariff.
4.0 Service under this agreement shall commence on the later of (l) the requested service commencement date, or (2) the date on which construction of any Direct Assignment Facilities and/or Network Upgrades are completed, or (3) such other date as it is permitted to become effective by the Commission. Service under this agreement shall terminate on such date as mutually agreed upon by the parties.
5.0 The Tie Line Owner agrees to provide and the Transmission Customer agrees to take and pay for Firm Point-To-Point Transmission Service in accordance with the provisions of Part II of the Tariff and this Service Agreement.
6.0 Any notice or request made to or by either Party regarding this Service Agreement shall be made to the representative of the other Party as indicated below. Tie Line Owner:
Wilderness Line Holdings, LLC c/o OATT Administrator nd 437 Madison Avenue, 22 Floor New York, NY 10022
Transmission Customer:
Windstar Energy, LLC c/o Alana Steele 3500 Glenrose Ave Altadena, CA 91001 (626) 755-4716 (626) 755-4175
7.0 The Tariff is incorporated herein and made a part hereof.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Service Agreement to be executed by their respective authorized officials.
